&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Position&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Project Manager will play a critical role on the SureAdhere Customer Success team, driving successful software implementations and long-term value for our diverse clients across public health and clinical trials. This position is designed for an agile, highly curious professional who is a strong project manager with a deep interest in data, clinical trial operations, and technology. In this role, as an expert in the SureAdhere product, you will act as a pivotal link between our technology and real-world impact, ensuring that digital health and adherence programs run smoothly.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A significant portion of your day-to-day work will involve direct, hands-on execution. This is a role for a collaborative problem-solver who possesses the patience to dive deep into complex data investigations, the adaptability to test and optimize technical features alongside our development team, and the drive to constantly improve team processes and client enablement by leveraging modern digital tools, including AI and data analytics platform integrations. While the majority of this role is focused on supporting the SureAdhere clinical trials portfolio, you will also play a critical role in supporting our public health clients throughout their lifecycle.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location and Travel&lt;/strong&gt;: This position is fully remote, based in South Africa with at least 3 hour daily overlap with US Eastern Time. This may occasionally include the need to take early or late calls to overlap with other timezones. This position requires regular travel, up to 20% for client visits, team working sessions, and conferences.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Clinical Trials Project Management &amp;amp; Delivery (Project Ownership &amp;amp; Collaboration)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;End-to-End Implementation:&lt;/strong&gt; Act as the primary project manager for mid-sized workstreams and SaaS client accounts. Manage project plans, coordinate timelines, and ensure deliverable milestones are met on time and within scope.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Complex Project Support:&lt;/strong&gt; Work closely with the rest of the SureAdhere team to support high-stakes, large-scale clinical trials and enterprise-level deployments, owning specific deliverables, tasks, and site readiness workstreams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Risk &amp;amp; Issue Mitigation:&lt;/strong&gt; Proactively identify project implementation risks, track roadblocks, and develop tactical mitigation plans to keep client programs running smoothly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Public Health Client Success &amp;amp; Onboarding&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sales Enablement:&lt;/strong&gt; Support the Partnerships team in responding to future/current client questions, developing responses to RFPs, and assisting with demos or other external meetings/events.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Manage Onboarding:&lt;/strong&gt; Lead the end-to-end onboarding process for new public health SaaS partners, helping them seamlessly transition from sales to active platform utilization.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Proactive Account Management:&lt;/strong&gt; Own regular touchpoints and strategic check-ins with public health clients, tracking usage metrics, assessing account health, identifying opportunities for program expansion (upselling/cross-selling), and ensuring high platform retention.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
